-- U.S. Stocks Pare Losses as Boehner ‘Optimistic’ on Budget Talks
-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 2012-11-28T15:39:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-28/u-s-stocks-pare-losses-as-boehner-optimistic-on-budget-talks.html
U.S. stocks pared losses as Speaker
of the House John Boehner said he is “optimistic” budget talks
with President  Barack Obama  will continue.  The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index slipped less than 0.2
percent to 1,396.38 at 10:38 a.m. in New York after sliding as
much as 1 percent earlier.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
